body_raw:
Let $(M,g)$ be an arbitrary smooth Riemannian manifold of $n$ dimensional and $p_0\in M$. $
abla$ denotes the Levi Civita connection. It is well known that there is a coordinate chart around $p_0$ s.t.   egin{eqnarray} & g_{ij}(p_0)=\delta_{ij}\ & 
abla_{ rac{\partial}{\partial x^i}}\dfrac{\partial}{\partial x^j}(p_0)=0\ \ \ (i,j=1,\cdots, n).  \end{eqnarray} "Riemannian normal coordinate chart centered at $p_0$" is one of them. Can we take a coordinate chart $(U;x^1,\cdots,x^n)$ around $p_0$ s.t.   egin{eqnarray} & g_{ij}(p_0)=\delta_{ij}\ & 
abla_{ rac{\partial}{\partial x^i}}\dfrac{\partial}{\partial x^j}(p_0)=0\ & \sum_{k=1}^n
abla_{ rac{\partial}{\partial x^k}}
abla_{ rac{\partial}{\partial x^k}}\dfrac{\partial}{\partial x^j}(p_0)=0\ -(i,j=1,\cdots, n)? \end{eqnarray}

